    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Chairs with back splats in the form of a lyre, a Regency period motif popularized by Adam, Hepplewhite, Sheraton, and Duncan Phyfe.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
